00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:09,310
I want to go back.

572
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:10,960
I'm sorry.

573
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:12,950
I don't even know how you travelled here,

574
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:14,940
let alone sending you back.

575
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:18,230
[Ten years ago?]

576
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:22,390
[She is the best specimen
for time travel research.]

577
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:23,800
Prof Chen.

578
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:26,150
Will the magnetic field on Chu Xia
affect medical equipment?

579
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:28,080
For example, artificial pacemakers.

580
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:28,960
Of course.

581
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:30,600
Once her emotion is agitated,

582
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:32,280
it will affect electronic products.

583
00:28:32,360 --> 00:28:35,520
For example, the lights were blinking.

584
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,800
It was caused by her emotional agitation.

585
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:39,550
However, you don't have to worry.

586
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:41,360
I have moved important equipment

587
00:28:41,440 --> 00:28:42,630
to the next room.

588
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:44,710
Hold on, don't be reckless.

589
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:47,430
Be patient.

590
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:50,510
Is there any way

591
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:52,590
to control the influence?

592
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:54,920
Technically,

593
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:57,920
as long as you stay calm,

594
00:28:58,000 --> 00:28:59,270
it won't affect anything.

595
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:00,910
However, I think it's impossible.

596
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:02,470
She is just a human.

597
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:05,190
Every human has mood swings.

598
00:29:06,080 --> 00:29:07,000
In short,

599
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:08,080
I can't move around freely

600
00:29:08,160 --> 00:29:09,750
or meet my parents.

601
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:13,190
You don't have to be so pessimistic.

602
00:29:13,280 --> 00:29:15,190
You are in luck because you ran into me.

603
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:17,100
I can try to find a solution

604
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:20,630
by inventing a device that
can control your energy.

605
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:22,240
With that device,

606
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:23,800
your range of activities can be expanded.

607
00:29:23,880 --> 00:29:25,400
Then, you can leave him.

608
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:26,440
However,

609
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:28,630
there is a minor technical issue.

610
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:32,470
This research requires
a huge amount of money.

611
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:35,760
My lab is a little short on funds.

612
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:36,680
That means

613
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:38,710
it can be solved with money.

614
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:43,520
We accept Alipay, Wechat, cash, cheques,

615
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:45,870
shares, gold and futures.

616
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:48,630
Stop looking at him. He is stingy.

617
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:49,870
I will figure it out.

618
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:02,400
You have been jumping for half an hour.

619
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:03,980
Do you need a break?

620
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:05,520
I fell at this spot.

621
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:07,060
I should be able to go back
the same way, right?

622
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:10,540
Apparently it's against Newton's Law.

623
00:30:10,640 --> 00:30:12,070
No way it works.

624
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:14,350
Why don't you jump off the building?

625
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:21,630
Stop! I was just kidding!

626
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,230
Are you crazy?

627
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:24,980
Is that a suicide attempt?

628
00:30:25,120 --> 00:30:26,360
I need to go back.

629
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:27,800
I want to be with my parents.

630
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:28,680
No.

631
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:30,680
That night, you

632
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:32,310
fell into my arms all of a sudden.

633
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:37,420
Hold on.

634
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:39,670
Where are you going?

635
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:44,550
Don't move.

636
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:47,990
What are you doing?

637
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:01,230
What nonsense is this?

638
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,550
You almost killed me. Get up.

639
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:06,510
Why isn't it working?

640
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:12,300
You appeared on the night
of the Super Moon.

641
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,200
Why don't...

642
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:14,080
Why don't we wait

643
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:16,070
for the next Super Moon night?

644
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:18,630
[The last Super Moon for the year]

645
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:19,520
[was over.]

646
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:21,480
[According to the Saros cycle,]

647
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:23,560
[the next Super Moon]

648
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,160
[is estimated to take place in
the year 2034.]

649
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:29,430
Why don't we try it again in 2034?

650
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:30,710
Are you out of your mind?

651
00:31:41,120 --> 00:31:42,950
I don't get it.

652
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:45,670
Why must the most bizarre thing

653
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:47,310
happen to me?

654
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:55,630
To me, this world

655
00:31:56,720 --> 00:31:58,510
is like a mirage.

656
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:02,270
I can see it yet I can't reach it.

657
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:05,790
But why?

658
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:21,870
Are you listening?
Why did this happen to me?

659
00:32:22,360 --> 00:32:23,160
I...

660
00:32:23,520 --> 00:32:24,640
I am expressing my feelings.

661
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:25,440
Why are you ignoring me?

662
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:26,550
What are you doing?

663
00:32:29,360 --> 00:32:30,470
Do you know?

664
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:32,710
In the virtual cyberworld,

665
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:34,230
it's all about binary,

666
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:37,230
which means everything
is formed by zeros and ones.

667
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:40,590
The game you play called
Battle of the Saints

668
00:32:41,320 --> 00:32:42,520
is basically

669
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:45,110
a collection of zeros and ones.

670
00:32:46,560 --> 00:32:48,880
Now, I'm using

671
00:32:48,960 --> 00:32:50,990
many black and white boxes

672
00:32:51,080 --> 00:32:52,280
that correspond to zeros and ones

673
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:54,360
to form

674
00:32:54,440 --> 00:32:56,190
an organised pattern

675
00:32:56,280 --> 00:32:57,790
of blacks and whites.

676
00:32:59,480 --> 00:33:01,950
It represents a certain thing.

677
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:23,240
Come here.

678
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:24,710
Why?

679
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:31,030
Put it here.

680
00:33:38,840 --> 00:33:39,870
Then?

681
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:42,750
Scan it.

682
00:33:43,560 --> 00:33:44,870
Scan it?

683
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:46,750
It is as if you are taking a photo.

684
00:33:47,240 --> 00:33:48,270
Scan it.

685
00:33:55,640 --> 00:33:56,790
How did you make it?

686
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:58,610
[Lei Chu Xia]

687
00:34:03,239 --> 00:34:04,590
When I was young,

688
00:34:04,719 --> 00:34:06,710
my dad always played this game with me.

689
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:09,280
It's known as the

690
00:34:09,679 --> 00:34:12,550
Two Dimensional Barcode Colouring Game.

691
00:34:14,560 --> 00:34:17,030
I still remember that he
used to be busy all the time.

692
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:20,590
I always bugged him to play with me.

693
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:22,400
So, he got me

694
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:25,150
some black and white boxes.

695
00:34:25,239 --> 00:34:27,310
If I got the code right,

696
00:34:27,719 --> 00:34:29,870
he would spend ten minutes
to keep me company.

697
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:34,550
In the beginning,

698
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:37,060
I didn't know how to do it.

699
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:39,469
Slowly, I mastered the pattern.

700
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:42,110
However, I knew that he was busy.

701
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:43,510
So, I pretend that I
didn't know how to do it.

702
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:45,420
I spent a long time arranging
the code on purpose.

703
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:48,590
I bet you miss your dad a lot.

704
00:34:51,680 --> 00:34:53,430
In the cyberworld, zero and one

705
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:54,400
is the most basic

706
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:55,790
yet the most important.

707
00:34:57,040 --> 00:34:58,510
Therefore, in your world,

708
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:00,230
you are the most important.

709
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:02,350
As long as you are here,

710
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:03,840
no matter where you came from,

711
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:04,760
no matter who you are

712
00:35:04,840 --> 00:35:06,630
or what your name is,

713
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:08,590
those are not important.

714
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:10,680
Just like the bar code,

715
00:35:10,770 --> 00:35:12,310
you can find the meaning of your presence.

716
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:13,600
You can create

717
00:35:13,680 --> 00:35:15,790
a new world that belongs to you.

718
00:35:18,470 --> 00:35:22,820
♫ Stepping on the galaxy ♫

719
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:26,020
Hello, Lei Chu Xia.

720
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:28,110
Nice to meet you.

721
00:35:32,160 --> 00:35:33,670
Hello, Xu Xiao Dong.

722
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,160
Nice to meet you too.

723
00:35:38,800 --> 00:35:41,490
♫ I come from the summer
while you come from the winter ♫

724
00:35:41,570 --> 00:35:43,120
♫ Let's meet in the autumn ♫

725
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:45,480
♫ Before the falling leaves ♫

726
00:35:45,750 --> 00:35:49,090
♫ Let's meet again ♫

727
00:35:49,790 --> 00:35:56,750
♫ Those who have met will meet again ♫

728
00:35:56,920 --> 00:35:58,950
♫ Some day ♫

729
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:32,550
[It's been ten years.]

730
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:35,950
[I wake up from a nightmare every night.]

731
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:37,910
[I'm almost out of breath.]

732
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:41,630
[I have done everything I could]

733
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:43,750
[so that I can forget you.]

734
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:46,390
[By organising the memorial service,]

735
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:49,910
[I thought I could bid you goodbye.]

736
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:51,870
[I didn't expect]

737
00:36:52,680 --> 00:36:55,550
[to see you in real life.]

738
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:57,640
[Chu Xia.]

739
00:36:57,840 --> 00:36:59,630
[Who are you? Let go of me!]

740
00:37:01,560 --> 00:37:02,720
[Are you turning my nightmare]

741
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:04,710
[into the reality]

742
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:07,190
[or are you turning the reality]

743
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:09,510
[into my nightmare?]

744
00:37:24,120 --> 00:37:25,350
It's time to eat.

745
00:37:25,520 --> 00:37:26,400
You must be starving.

746
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:28,310
Here, try it.

747
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:36,030
What do you think?

748
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:38,470
It's a little too sweet.

749
00:37:40,190 --> 00:37:41,380
[You have a new message]

750
00:37:44,040 --> 00:37:46,190
Chu Xia, your mum has been discharged.

751
00:37:46,830 --> 00:37:51,230
[Please come to the hospital
to fill the discharge papers.]

752
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,870
I wish to see her.

753
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:56,310
I'll see her from afar.

754
00:37:57,360 --> 00:37:59,720
Okay, I'll bring you there.

755
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:00,750
Okay.

756
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:06,430
We are home.

757
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:20,990
The street lamp stopped
working for a long time.

758
00:38:21,560 --> 00:38:23,350
Why isn't it fixed yet?

759
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:24,600
It's an old residential area.

760
00:38:24,680 --> 00:38:26,310
That's normal.

761
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:27,440
Darling.

762
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:29,310
Here, let me help you.

763
00:38:30,160 --> 00:38:32,830
I can walk on my own.
I don't need your help.

764
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:34,230
Why don't you hold my hand?

765
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:36,350
It's dark, I can't see clearly.

766
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:37,710
Hold my hand.

767
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:41,540
Here, slow down.

768
00:39:03,360 --> 00:39:04,160
Since when

769
00:39:04,240 --> 00:39:05,830
can street lamps be controlled by voice?

770
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:09,800
It's too bright. It's dazzling.

771
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:11,320
Hold my hand.

772
00:39:11,400 --> 00:39:13,030
I am holding your hand, am I not?

773
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:22,920
[Dad, I lost my way.]

774
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:23,680
[Dad.]

775
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:28,640
[I couldn't find my way home.]

776
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:32,000
[Dad, I lost my way.]

777
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,070
[Chu Xia.]

778
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:37,760
[Here, let me hug you.]

779
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:38,640
[Don't cry.]

780
00:39:38,720 --> 00:39:39,830
[I'm here.]

781
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,310
[Sit down and tell me.]

782
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:44,800
[What happened?]

783
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:45,600
[Dad.]

784
00:39:45,680 --> 00:39:49,420
[I couldn't find my way home.]

785
00:39:51,160 --> 00:39:52,920
[We've moved here for a month now.]

786
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:53,840
[Why can't you]

787
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:55,240
[remember the way home?]

788
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:57,750
[What should I do?]

789
00:39:58,800 --> 00:40:00,420
[I have an idea.]

790
00:40:00,960 --> 00:40:02,470
[Let's]

791
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:04,390
[paint the staircases]

792
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:06,680
[into the colours of a rainbow.]

793
00:40:06,760 --> 00:40:07,870
[Okay?]

794
00:40:09,560 --> 00:40:10,280
[Moving forward,]

795
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:11,240
[we shall call it]

796
00:40:11,360 --> 00:40:13,030
[the rainbow staircase, okay?]

797
00:40:13,160 --> 00:40:16,150
The rainbow staircase looks like candy.

798
00:40:16,240 --> 00:40:18,080
It's so beautiful.

799
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:19,230
It's beautiful, right?

800
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:22,110
We shall repaint it every year.

801
00:40:22,200 --> 00:40:23,240
In that case,

802
00:40:23,360 --> 00:40:24,320
you will never

803
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:26,670
lose your way again.

804
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:37,310
[Xiao Dong.]

805
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:38,990
Is that girl with you?

806
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:41,580
Yes, she is with me.

807
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:43,120
By the way, Professor Chen,

808
00:40:43,290 --> 00:40:44,130
she has a name now.

809
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:45,750
[Her name is Lei Chu Xia.]

810
00:40:46,110 --> 00:40:46,990
Lei Chu Xia?

811
00:40:47,080 --> 00:40:48,600
This name is quite romantic.

812
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:51,110
Sure, let me talk to Lei Chu Xia.

813
00:40:51,190 --> 00:40:51,920
I have good news for her.

814
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:52,870
Okay.

815
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:56,510
Professor Chen is on the line.

816
00:40:57,160 --> 00:40:58,470
Professor Chen?

817
00:41:01,040 --> 00:41:02,110
Professor Chen.
